name: Dandahra Canyon
description:
Introduction

Flow gauge downstream: https://waterinsights.waternsw.com.au/17759-dandahra-creek/river-data#204056

Approach

Descent

• 7 hours car to car

• Start at mulligans campground, walk to barra nula cascades and get in creek there. Easy creek walking, then starts to get slightly more vertical.

• Jump - 6m - creek centre

• Jump - 7m - creek left

• Slotty section - we bypassed on CL and down climbed and then did small 3m jump at the end. However, it should be bolted. There is a waterfall, could easily add some bolts just to the right of this and abseil down. There are then two siphons - the first one you can climb up and around on the rock, the second one you could easily just swim through at the water levels we did it at (90.7ML/day).

• Bit more easy creek walking until you get to where Dandahra Falls starts

• R1 - 25m - CL - single bolt. Make sure to bleed the rope for this one - rock is very sharp!

• R2 - 40m - CL. Abseil down to where there is a nose at creek centre - this is where the next bolts are

• R3 - 65m - creek left / centre on the nose. Rooster tail pitch - waterfall will be shooting up on the right. Abseil down into pool which is flushing over and then exit on CL

• R4 - 15m - CL of pool. Rock is very slippery at anchor. Abseil down CL against wall, there is another anchor just around the corner where the wall ends.

• R5 - 25m - CL. Abseil down to where sheer vertical wall begins.

• R6 - 20m - CL. Abseil down on edge of flow - next anchor is just around the corner of the wall.

• R7 - 25m - CL. Abseil leftwards down to ledge

• Traverse - 5m - across ledge to another double bolt anchor

• R8 - 40m or less - CL. Includes bolt for redirect about 5m down - rig retrievable redirect. Abseil all the way down to the hanging rebelay anchor.

• R9 - 35m or less - CL. Anchor is a full hanging rebelay - uncomfortable to wait at. Abseil all the way down into pool at the bottom - could do a floating bag anchor in high flow to guide you across the pool.

• Swim out pool, walk down creek through boulders for like 50m. Prominent ridge which is next to canyon comes down and meets the creek, there are a few small trees. This is where the first climb is.

• First climb - maybe about 5 bolts or so, climb up to tree and can then anchor off tree to belay everyone else. Then walk up the ridge and there is the second climb almost immediately.

• Second climb - awkward boulder, there are 3 bolts you can use to aid your climb up the boulder.

• Then just follow ridge up to where the lookout is. Ridge has lots of loose rock, rock is also very brittle so it breaks easily - be careful. We generally stuck to the right hand side of the ridge and this was pretty good. Once you get to the lookout, there is a track to take you back to the campsite
